The blockade call by the International Transport Workers’ Federation helped to get the steelmen’s strike off to a strong start. Although there was a near 100 percent response, there was criticism from the unions that no ballot was held. 23 years ago (2000) Police revealed a £3million painting by French post-impressionist Paul Cezanne was stolen from Oxford’s Ashmolean Museum in a daring rooftop raid on New Year’s Eve. Theories included that it might have been stolen to order. The work has never been recovered. Three years ago (2020) Iranian General Qasem Soleimani was killed by an American drone strike near Baghdad International Airport sparking fears of retaliation by the Iranians who declared it an act of terrorism. The assassination came after US President Donald Trump withdrew from the 2015 Iran nuclear deal and reimposed sanctions on the country.